content: Simple yet feature-rich slideshow program, everything you need for personal or business use. Fast and friendly support from developer!
This desperately needs a widget to display photos in a picture frame. If you can tag photos in here that will be cool also

GFolio has given me just about everything I wanted from Google Drive. Slideshows, quick loading, a randomize button, gif and video compatibility without a hitch, etc. Plus there's a bunch of cool bells and whistles like the transitions! I dig it. Good purchase.
very good and thank you
Good one but had to go for refund as the minimum refresh interval is too high for me at 3 minutes. Will purchase if it can also be configured to few seconds.
video from Google drive not playing in this app
replyContent: Please write to me at snapwood@snapwoodapps.com so I can learn about your video and why it may not be playing.  Thanks!

content: Upload to Google Drive™ Without Wifi being necessary. Yes, upload to Google Drive with having to just need... mobile data ONLY!
Great app to store all your photos from Google. I love it very much, just a click away and you have all your photos.
A better solution to Google photos

Really good viewer for photos stored in Goggle drive. The initial download of all thumbnails and photos will take a while. Afterwards, everything will be cached and fast. Can also do upload of photos taken by the phone to Google drive .

Missing option to delete cache of viewed photos while keeping cache of downloaded thumbnails. Needed if you have >50000 thumbnails and don't want to redownload all just for clearing downloaded photos.
Would be nice if thumbnails showed whole file name.
Nice App

This app is fantastic -- as are the other related apps for similar services from Snapwood. They are super simple to setup -- just log into your Google Account -- and then the app syncs everything up with tons of user-friendly options to customize the way the photos are displayed. Not only that, but the developer provides fantastic support via email. Can't recommend, enough, if you're looking to keep your Google Drive or Google Photos in sync on your android device
Great app but can't use external storage - is this possible?!
Great app, loved the download thumbnails only mode.  Is there a way to change the folder icon that gets generated automatically?
Efficient way to move images into gallery from Drive.
Only loads a few of my photos
Really like this app, best Google drive photos viewer
love it
Also doesn't allow multiple folders in same slideshow. Getting refund..
The ability to view RAW images in my Google Drive archive has made this app invaluable for me. Thank you very much!
Trust me when I say I have tried them all.... This company makes the best apps for accessing all your cloud storage... Wish they made apps for Windows 8...
Like how the app retains folder structure!

Good app but it's slow on large albums (700+ pics). It takes 5 secs to enter the album and another 5 to see the first picture. After that it's instant. All pictures are downloaded so connectivity shouldn't be the problem. Smaller albums with less photo's (<200 pics) are loading fast. My phone is fast enough (nexus 5). Also: the thumbnails are a bit small. Would be nice if the gridsize could be altered.

This app should be way more popular. I decided to keep ALL of my photos to Google Drive so, in addition to GDrive app functions I needed the following: 1. Attractive way to view GDrive photos. 2. Quick and easy way to organize: Create/delete folders & files, move/copy with MULTI SELECT (not available in GD). 3. Instant backup Nexus 5 camera>GDrive (not in GD app either). Unfortunately I had already bought another app just for that. This app does all these so is perfect all-in-one supplement to GDrive app!
Does exactly what I need it to do.

Few things what is not include: video not support, can not send link to image or folder. Strange but on Picasa or Flicr is working but on Google Drive not. Api Google is allow this so developer need to add this. And sort by data take is not working Its mish mash.

I tried out several slideshow apps before I landed on this one.  It has clear options and lots of them. It runs smoothly and is well-designed.  I have it hooked up to Google Drive, and by using EmailItIn, I am having the grandkids email photos to grandma, and then she can view them as a slideshow in gFolio.  It is so simple, she will find it easy to use.
HTC one x
Does exactly as advertised. I hope to see maybe widget options in the future to display pictures as well.
Not the greatest for a large library, goes black and says "downloading" between some photos when slideshow playing
replyContent: Once the app is allowed to auto download, you will no longer see the "downloading" message for photos that are not locally cached.

content: No more choosing between Picasa and g+. This combined with folder sync, let's you auto backup to g drive and easily access your photos anywhere at anytime. Great great app. Easy to use and on the eye.
Only request though would be for photo gallery view on phone to mimic tablet.. No filenames just larger thumbnails

I must say I was quite skeptical about buying this app and especially a*** about giveng 5 stars when  I saw a review with one star I decided to give the benefit of the doubt im glad i made the purchase app works awesome I haven't tried the download for off line yet  part  but uploading pictures awesome been looking for an app like this for a while keep up the good work nice piece.. So 4 Stars for now let's see what else is in store... In my opinion worth the $3 dollers
Simple and easy
Absolutely best customer service I have seen in app stores including from Apple on my ipad. App looks great on my nexus 7. Thanks Brian!
The app fails to work if files are in root directory.  Move them to folders and app works seemless.
Love drop box app however this one fails
replyContent: Please contact me at snapwood@snapwoodapps.com.  I can not provide support through Google Play's review mechanism.

content: Most of the time it never launches. A lot of this ties to the storage location on your phone which it maxes out quickly. It would be nice to change it from the SD card. However, if you want to use an alternative location expect you to be able to type in the:// backslash backslash semi: space blah blah blah and which the heck. Can do that?
replyContent: Could you email me at snapwood@snapwoodapps.com so I can help you or off you a refund?

Puedo ver las fotos que tengo en google drive, y compartirlas con quien quiera.
I love the app. It loads pix quickly and they are viewable even when I don't have network service.
Sorting and searching is weak
This app looks great,  but the functionality is not there.  If you have large numbers of photos as I do then this app is likely not for you.
It will upload videos but they don't show up in the gallery for playback.

Nice app, the only drawback is that it doesn't store the original photos on the device, but rather lower resolution versions. The quality suffers in the conversion and it's impossible to zoom in. There needs to be an option for this, otherwise the app is useless to me.

I have been looking for an app for this since Google drive first launched. Now I don't have to store photos in multiple locations (picasa, drive and Google plus). I can keep everything on drive and browse all of my photos, edit them and download them all from one app. Awesome!

I am loving this app! If you want to use Google Drive to store your photos, this app is great for viewing those photos. I downloaded my photos to my tab for offline viewing. The interface is great, and the app runs silky smooth. Also a huge thumbs up for a great developer! I can easily recommend this app!
Fast and elegant! Friendly developer.
